source: Matt Innis for US Senate, Inc.
text: According to Rep. Al Green (D-Texas), “…the genesis of impeachment, to be very candid with you, was when the president was running for office and he had members of his own party to talk about his unfitness to hold office.” Who was one of those “members of his own party” calling the president unfit? That’s right - Ben Sasse. Sasse repeatedly called Trump “unfit” while on Jake Tappers’ CNN show during the 2016 campaign and after Trump was elected, giving Democrats the incentive for the flawed impeachment process.  Sasse also gave cover to the Democrats and liberal media regarding the whistleblower report - prior to the release of the transcript - when he stated that “Republicans ought not to be rushing to circle the wagons…when there’s obviously lots troubling in there.” It’s obvious that the liberals are taking their cues from people like Ben Sasse; his lack of respect for the President certainly doesn’t reflect my values and, from what I’ve been hearing from virtually everyone I talk with as I travel the state, he doesn’t reflect the values of conservative Nebraskans, either. Clearly, it’s time for Nebraskans to make a change.

text: I don’t believe our Framers intended for us to have career politicians. They intended for us to have representatives, but instead, we’ve created a ruling class. When we allow individuals to serve 30, 40, 50 and nearly 60 years in Congress or any office, the nation loses because they are only interested in keeping their power. I supported the successful local term limits petition in Lincoln on the Mayor. I support a measure that would limit Members of Congress to two six-year terms in the U.S. Senate and six two-year terms in the House of Representatives, allowing a person to serve 12 years in each office. A person would have to sit out for six years, and if they wanted to run again for the same seat, they could do so.
